text: Camino Real from the mission of Quinchilca to the indigenous reduction of Puconu according to the map prepared by the expedition of Francisco Vidal Gormaz in 1869. Pucono or Puconu is a hamlet in the left and southern bank of San Pedro River, Los Lagos commune, southern Chile. ==References== Category:Geography of Los Ríos Region Category:Populated places in Valdivia Province
title: Pucono
